HEADWORD: Unbar
<hw>Un*bar"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>bar</ets>.]</ety> <def>To remove a bar or bars
from; to unbolt; to open; <as>as, to <ex>unbar</ex> a gate</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Heber.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unbarbed</ent>⟦br⟧
